<div class="artist-banner" style="background-image: url('<%= cl_image_path @artist.photo %>');" >
</div>
<div class="container artist_show">
  <div class="img_artist">
    <%= image_tag "chuck.jpg" %>
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-8 bloc_name">
    <h1><%= @artist.name %></h1>
    <h4><%= @artist.category.name %></h4>
    <h4><%= @artist.public.label %></h4>
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-12 card_artist">
    <div class="col-xs-4 bloc_detail">
      <span><i class="far fa-address-book"></i></span>
      <p class="label_icon">Description</p>
      <p><%= @artist.description%></p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-4 bloc_detail">
      <span><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i></span>
      <p class="label_icon">Address</p>
      <p><%= @artist.address%></p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-4 bloc_detail">
      <span><i class="fas fa-dollar-sign"></i></span>
      <p class="label_icon">Price</p>
      <p><%= @artist.hour_rate%>â‚¬/heure</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-12 card_about">
    <h1>About me</h1>
<p>Now that we know who you are, I know who I am. I'm not a mistake! It all makes sense! In a comic, you know how you can tell who the arch-villain's going to be? He's the exact opposite of the hero. And most times they're friends, like you and me! I should've known way back when... You know why, David? Because of the kids. They called me Mr Glass. </p>
  </div>
  <div
  id="map"
  style="width: 100%;
  height: 600px;"
  data-markers="<%= @markers.to_json %>"
  ></div>
  <div class="col-xs-12 card_booking">
    <h1>Book me!</h1>
    <p>Form here to book an artist</p>
    <button type="button" name="button" class="book_btn btn btn-primary">Book now</button>
  </div>

  <div class="col-xs-12 form_booking">
    <%= simple_form_for [@artist, @booking] do |f| %>
    <%= f.input :check_in, as: :datetime, html5: true %>
    <%= f.input :check_out, as: :datetime, html5: true %>
    <%= f.submit "Confirm booking", class: "btn btn-success" %>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>
